MY NECK AROUND.

20:36.931 --> 20:39.673
-IT'S ALL RIGHT.
ALL YOU GOTTA DO IS...

20:39.803 --> 20:41.457
-I KNOW. I KNOW.

20:41.588 --> 20:42.415
"FEED ME."
-FEED ME.

20:42.545 --> 20:44.025
-"FEED ME."

20:44.155 --> 20:45.592
-HOW DO YOU KNOW HE'S A COP?

20:45.722 --> 20:47.071
-HE WAS FRIENDS WITH TITO.

20:47.202 --> 20:48.638
-SO?

20:48.769 --> 20:51.075
-SO, WHAT'S HE DOING HERE?

20:51.206 --> 20:53.730
YOU THINK
IT'S JUST A COINCIDENCE
THAT HE SHOWED UP?

20:53.861 --> 20:56.777
PEOPLE SAW YOU FIGHTING
WITH TITO BEFORE HE DIED.

21:02.783 --> 21:04.263
LET'S GET OUT OF HERE.

21:04.393 --> 21:06.177
LEAVE TOWN BEFORE
THEY PUT IT ALL TOGETHER.

21:06.308 --> 21:08.179
THERE'S NO REASON
FOR US TO STICK AROUND.

21:08.310 --> 21:10.921
-THERE'S NO REASON
FOR US TO LEAVE.
JUST BE COOL.

21:11.052 --> 21:12.749
NOBODY IS GONNA TOUCH US.

21:12.880 --> 21:14.098
YOU'RE GONNA GET THE MONEY,

21:14.229 --> 21:16.362
AND WE'LL LIVE
HAPPILY EVER AFTER.

21:17.014 --> 21:17.928
-HMM.

21:26.720 --> 21:28.591
-MITCH, GET READY
TO PLAY SOME D.

21:28.722 --> 21:30.593
-I'M ON HIM. I'M ON HIM.

21:37.034 --> 21:38.340
-MITCH! MITCH! MITCH!

21:43.040 --> 21:44.346
-YES!

21:45.739 --> 21:46.914
YES!

21:52.876 --> 21:55.923
-THANK YOU, MY MAN. ALL RIGHT.

22:02.799 --> 22:04.410
NOW, THAT WAS BASKETBALL, MITCH.

22:04.540 --> 22:06.107
HELL OF GAME.

22:06.237 --> 22:08.936
WHAT CANE YOU SAY
ABOUT THE CAGEY, OLD VETERAN?

22:09.066 --> 22:10.459
HE DID IT AGAIN.

22:10.590 --> 22:12.548
-NO MORE HUSTLING, OZ.

22:12.679 --> 22:15.029
LOOK, THE DEAL WAS
WE WIN, YOU TALK.
SO, NOW, WHAT YOU GOT?

22:15.159 --> 22:17.553
MY BODY IS
ONE GIANT CHARLEY HORSE,
SO LET'S HEAR IT.

22:19.990 --> 22:21.340
WHAT IS THIS?
WHAT ARE YOU GIVING ME?

22:22.819 --> 22:24.343
-THAT'S IT.

22:24.473 --> 22:25.822
-WHAT DOES THIS HAVE TO DO
WITH TITO WASHBURN?

22:25.953 --> 22:28.172
-WHAT'S IT SAY?
JUST READ IT. WHAT'S IT SAY?

22:28.303 --> 22:30.261
-"MELVIN FREESTONE,
FOR ALL YOUR INSURANCE NEEDS,
FIRE, THEFT, AUTO...

22:33.526 --> 22:34.788
LIFE"?

22:34.918 --> 22:37.094
-YOU GOT IT.
SEE YOU LATER, BLOOD.

22:40.837 --> 22:42.056
-LIFE.

22:53.850 --> 22:55.286
-DENNIS: HEY... HEY!

22:56.592 --> 22:57.724
HELP!

23:14.784 --> 23:15.872
HELP!

23:19.354 --> 23:20.399
HELP!

23:21.791 --> 23:23.140
-HERE. TAKE THE CAN.

23:26.666 --> 23:27.710
I GOT YOU.

23:28.407 --> 23:29.495
-AH.

23:36.980 --> 23:39.113
WELL, I'M JUST LOOPY,
YOU KNOW?

23:39.243 --> 23:42.333
I THOUGHT FOR SURE THE LIGHTS...
THE LIGHTS WERE GOING OFF,
YOU KNOW?

23:42.464 --> 23:45.249
I JUST... EVERYTHING FELT
SO WARM AND FUZZY, AND I...

23:45.380 --> 23:48.470
AT ONE POINT, I SAW ALLIGATORS
PLAYING SAXOPHONES
AND STUFF LIKE THAT.

23:48.601 --> 23:50.603
THEN I LOOKED UP,
AND I SAW THIS BEAUTIFUL FACE.

23:51.212 --> 23:52.518
YOU LOOKED LIKE AN ANGEL.

23:53.301 --> 23:55.042
-WELL, YOU'VE DEFINITELY HAD
ENOUGH OXYGEN.
-YEAH.

23:55.172 --> 23:57.174
-HOW IS YOUR LEG?

23:57.305 --> 23:59.873
-WELL, IT'S WEAK.
I DON'T KNOW IF I CAN
PUT ANY PRESSURE ON IT.

24:00.003 --> 24:01.570
-WELL, I DIDN'T FIND
ANY BITE MARKS.

24:01.701 --> 24:03.354
SO TRY AND STAND UP.
-ALL RIGHT.

24:03.485 --> 24:05.356
-I'M SURE IT WAS
JUST A MUSCLE CRAMP.

24:05.835 --> 24:07.054
-OH!

24:07.184 --> 24:08.751
-HAVE I MET YOU
SOMEWHERE BEFORE?

24:08.882 --> 24:10.666
-YEAH, YESTERDAY. YOU REMEMBER?
YOU PICKED UP MY TRASH.

24:11.972 --> 24:13.843
-OKAY, THAT'S WHY
YOU LOOK FAMILIAR.

24:13.974 --> 24:16.019
-DENNIS KOSOWSKI.
-C.J. PARKER.

24:16.150 --> 24:17.673
-HOW YOU DOING?
-GOOD. THANKS.

24:17.804 --> 24:18.761
-YOU SURE ARE.

24:21.111 --> 24:23.331
-STEPHANIE:
YOU'RE GOING OUT
WITH A GUY YOU RESCUED?

24:23.462 --> 24:25.638
OH, C.J.,
THE LAST TIME YOU DID THAT,

24:25.768 --> 24:29.032
YOU SPENT THE ENTIRE EVENING
WATCHING SOME DORK PICK FLEAS
OFF HIS CAT.

24:29.163 --> 24:30.991
-WELL, DENNIS ISN'T A DORK.

24:31.121 --> 24:33.776
HE'S A CHARMING, SENSITIVE,
DOWN-TO-EARTH, NORMAL GUY.

24:33.907 --> 24:36.475
-RIGHT. THAT'S WHAT YOU SAID
ABOUT THE FLEA-PICKER.

24:38.520 --> 24:41.218
-GARNER: NO, THAT'LL BE FINE,
MR. FREESTONE. A COPY OF
THE POLICY IS ALL I NEED.

24:42.481 --> 24:44.526
YOU'VE BEEN A BIG HELP, SIR.
THANK YOU VERY MUCH.

24:45.222 --> 24:46.441
BYE.

24:47.181 --> 24:48.487
RIGHT. BYE.

24:49.966 --> 24:51.185
-WHAT'S THE SCOOP?

24:52.665 --> 24:54.667
-THREE YEARS AGO,
MELVIN FREESTONE WROTE

24:54.797 --> 24:57.626
A HALF-MILLION DOLLAR
LIFE INSURANCE POLICY
ON TITO WASHBURN.

24:57.757 --> 24:59.585
A SPORTS AGENT
TOOK IT OUT ON HIM

24:59.715 --> 25:01.369
WHEN IT LOOKED LIKE
HE'D PLAY PRO BALL.

25:02.065 --> 25:03.240
-THAT'S ILLEGAL.

25:04.285 --> 25:06.940
-THAT'S WHY NOBODY
KNEW ABOUT IT TILL NOW.

25:07.723 --> 25:09.769
-WELL, WHO'S THE BENEFICIARY?
HIS WIFE?

25:12.641 --> 25:13.816
YOU THINK SHE KILLED HIM?

25:16.906 --> 25:17.951
-WHAT'S THE MATTER, GUYS?

25:18.081 --> 25:19.169
A LITTLE SORE?

25:20.170 --> 25:21.345
DID YOU AT LEAST WIN THE GAME?

25:21.476 --> 25:23.478
-OF COURSE WE WON.

25:23.609 --> 25:25.349
-CONGRATULATIONS.

25:26.481 --> 25:28.657
GARNER, THERE WAS
A MESSAGE FOR YOU FROM THE LAB.

25:28.788 --> 25:31.530
THEY SAID THEY FOUND
A TRACE OF BLOOD
UNDER ONE OF TITO'S FINGERNAILS.

25:31.660 --> 25:33.401
IT EVIDENTIALLY WASN'T HIS.

25:34.010 --> 25:35.403
-IF TITO WAS MURDERED...

25:37.753 --> 25:39.320
-THIS COULD BE
THE BLOOD OF HIS KILLER.

25:39.842 --> 25:42.323
WE NEED TO PLAY
ANOTHER GAME, MITCH.

25:43.063 --> 25:45.674
-LOOK, HONEY,
THE CREAM IS WORKING.

25:48.459 --> 25:49.722
I'M GOING OUT TO LUNCH WITH YOU.

25:49.852 --> 25:51.854
-NO ARLENE,
YOU CAN'T DO THAT.

25:52.551 --> 25:54.727
-DENNIS, DO YOU REALIZE

25:54.857 --> 25:58.948
WE'VE SPENT THE GRAND TOTAL
OF 15 MINUTES TOGETHER
OUR ENTIRE HONEYMOON?

25:59.079 --> 26:01.603
-YEAH, BUT IF YOU GO DOWNSTAIRS,
ALL THEY HAVE IS
AN OPEN-AIR CAFE,

26:01.734 --> 26:03.474
AND YOU CAN'T SIT IN THE SUN.

26:03.605 --> 26:06.260
-ALL RIGHT,
SO WE'LL ORDER ROOM SERVICE.

26:06.390 --> 26:11.352
I'M NOT SPENDING A WHOLE DAY
COOPED UP IN THIS ROOM
ALL BY MYSELF AGAIN.

26:11.482 --> 26:12.962
-LOOK, ROOM SERVICE
COULD TAKE HOURS.

26:13.093 --> 26:14.355
IT'LL BE FOREVER
BEFORE THEY GET FOOD UP HERE.

26:14.485 --> 26:16.096
I'LL TELL YOU WHAT.

26:16.226 --> 26:18.272
I'LL RUN DOWN TO THE RESTAURANT.
I'LL GET US BOTH FOOD.

26:18.402 --> 26:20.404
I'LL BRING IT UP HERE.
IT'LL BE LIKE HAVING
A PICNIC AT THE BEACH.

26:20.535 --> 26:23.016
ISN'T THAT A GREAT IDEA?
IT'LL BE CHEAPER
AND MORE ROMANTIC.

26:23.146 --> 26:25.061
-OH, ALL RIGHT.

26:25.192 --> 26:26.454
BUT DON'T TAKE LONG.
-OKAY.

26:26.585 --> 26:28.587
-I'LL MISS YOU.
-I'LL MISS YOU, TOO.

26:28.717 --> 26:30.632
-GIVE ME A KISSIE.
-OKAY.

26:30.763 --> 26:32.547
WHAT DO YOU WANT?

26:32.678 --> 26:34.375
-I'LL HAVE A HAM AND CHEESE
SANDWICH ON A SOURDOUGH ROLL,

26:34.505 --> 26:38.161
LETTUCE, TOMATO, ONION,
HEAVY ON THE MUSTARD.

26:38.292 --> 26:40.555
-OKAY, THAT'S A HAM AND CHEESE
WITH EVERYTHING.
HOLD THE MUSTARD.

26:40.686 --> 26:42.165
I'LL BE BACK BEFORE YOU KNOW IT.

26:42.296 --> 26:44.298
-AND A DIET PEPSI.

26:45.560 --> 26:47.475
THAT WAS HEAVY ON THE MUSTARD.

26:57.485 --> 26:59.530
-I KNOW. "FEED ME."

27:00.619 --> 27:01.663
-YEAH.

27:25.121 --> 27:26.253
WHAT ARE THE ODDS?

27:26.383 --> 27:28.429
-YOU'RE 5-TO-1, UNDERDOGS.

27:28.559 --> 27:30.605
-HOW MUCH IS RIDING ON THE GAME?

27:30.736 --> 27:32.694
-EVERYTHING I GOT.

27:33.739 --> 27:35.305
I HOPE YOU CAME TO PLAY.

27:35.436 --> 27:37.743
-EXCUSE ME. NOT SO FAST.

27:38.569 --> 27:42.748
HOW WE PLAY DEPENDS A LOT
ON HOW MUCH YOU TELL US
ABOUT TITO WASHBURN.

27:43.966 --> 27:45.794
-WELL, I GOT NO PROBLEM
WITH THAT, SEE.

27:46.708 --> 27:50.103
SEE, THE WORD ON THE STREET IS
COOKIE WAS SEEING SOMEBODY
ON THE SIDE.

27:50.233 --> 27:52.627
-YOU WOULDN'T HAPPEN TO KNOW
WHO THAT SOMEBODY ELSE IS,
WOULD YOU?

27:53.367 --> 27:54.934
-YEAH, THAT DUDE
RIGHT OVER THERE,

27:55.064 --> 27:57.763
THE ONE YOU'RE PLAYING AGAINST.
NAME IS TREY HARRIS.

27:57.893 --> 28:00.722
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

28:06.554 --> 28:07.816
-I'LL TAKE THE WHITE GUY.

28:13.126 --> 28:17.043
-[ETHEREAL MUSIC PLAYING]

28:47.682 --> 28:48.944
-[EXHALES]

28:59.694 --> 29:01.043
HI.
-HI.

29:01.174 --> 29:03.263
OH, THANKS.
-OH, YEAH.

29:12.751 --> 29:13.969
YOU LOOK SENSATIONAL.

29:14.100 --> 29:15.884
-THANKS.

29:16.580 --> 29:18.931
-I CAN'T BELIEVE THAT
I'M ACTUALLY SITTING HERE
HAVING LUNCH WITH A GODDESS.

29:21.585 --> 29:23.326
WHERE HAVE YOU BEEN
ALL MY LIFE?

29:24.284 --> 29:25.764
-WELL, ACTUALLY,
RIGHT OUT THERE.

29:26.547 --> 29:27.809
-OH.

29:27.940 --> 29:30.203
-EXCUSE ME, SIR.
YOUR ORDER IS UP.

29:30.333 --> 29:32.335
-WHAT ORDER? WE HAVEN'T EVEN
LOOKED AT OUR MENUS.

29:32.466 --> 29:34.860
-UH, NO, ACTUALLY,
THIS IS FOR MY ASSISTANT.

29:34.990 --> 29:37.601
WE'RE ON KIND OF A DEADLINE,
SO I GOT HER A ROOM
HERE AT THE HOTEL.

29:37.732 --> 29:39.995
I'M JUST GONNA RUN
SOME FOOD UP TO HER.

29:40.126 --> 29:41.910
HEY, I TELL YOU WHAT.
WHY DON'T YOU ORDER FOR ME?
I LIKE EVERYTHING, OKAY?

29:42.041 --> 29:44.304
AND I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.
DON'T GO ANYWHERE.

29:53.269 --> 29:54.270
WHOA!

29:58.840 --> 30:01.800
-[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

30:03.758 --> 30:04.977
-[DENNIS FALLING]
-OH!

30:08.589 --> 30:10.852
HI, HONEY. HERE'S THE LUNCH.

30:10.983 --> 30:12.462
COME ON. SIT DOWN.
-OW.

30:12.593 --> 30:13.812
-HERE IT IS.

30:15.988 --> 30:17.554
-WHERE'S YOURS?

30:17.685 --> 30:19.469
-UH, IT WASN'T READY.
THEY SCREWED UP THE ORDER.

30:19.600 --> 30:21.167
THERE'S TERRIBLE SERVICE HERE.

30:21.297 --> 30:23.082
CAN YOU BELIEVE THIS?
I HAVE TO GO DOWNSTAIRS NOW.

30:24.344 --> 30:25.519
HOW ABOUT OUR LUCK, HUH?

30:26.476 --> 30:27.477
-WHAT DID YOU ORDER?

30:27.608 --> 30:29.262
-UH, CHICKEN SALAD.

30:29.392 --> 30:31.307
-I THOUGHT
YOU HATE CHICKEN SALAD.

30:31.438 --> 30:33.005
-NO, ACTUALLY, I HATE EGG SALAD.

30:34.006 --> 30:35.964
LOOK, I'LL TELL YOU WHAT.
YOU'RE HUNGRY. WHY DON'T YOU
GO AHEAD AND START?

30:36.095 --> 30:37.574
DON'T WAIT FOR ME, OKAY?

30:38.837 --> 30:39.968
-WAIT A MINUTE.

30:40.099 --> 30:41.578
WHERE'S MY DIET PEPSI?

30:41.709 --> 30:44.103
-UH, DIET PEPSI. OKAY.
DIET PEPSI.

30:46.235 --> 30:50.283
-[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

31:28.190 --> 31:29.496
-HERE YOU GO, HONEY.

31:30.410 --> 31:32.847
-WHAT? YOUR CHICKEN SALAD
ISN'T READY YET?

31:32.978 --> 31:35.241
-MY CHICKEN SALAD? [CHUCKLES]
THEY'RE OUT OF CHICKEN SALAD.

31:35.371 --> 31:37.852
NOW, I GOTTA GO BACK DOWN
AND TAKE A LOOK AT A MENU
DOWN THERE.

31:37.983 --> 31:39.985
CAN YOU BELIEVE THIS?
AND I REALLY FELT LIKE
CHICKEN SALAD, TOO.

31:40.115 --> 31:42.465
-ALL RIGHT, ENOUGH ALREADY.

31:42.596 --> 31:44.293
WE'LL SHARE MY SANDWICH.

31:44.424 --> 31:46.034
-NO, NO, I COULDN'T DO THAT.

31:46.165 --> 31:47.818
THIS IS YOUR SANDWICH.
I GOT THIS SANDWICH FOR YOU.

31:47.949 --> 31:50.082
I WANT YOU
TO TAKE THIS SANDWICH
AND ENJOY IT.

31:50.212 --> 31:52.823
IT'S PROBABLY A NOTHING ANYWAY.
IT'S A HOTEL SANDWICH.
IT'S A SMALL PORTION.

31:52.954 --> 31:55.217
YOU JUST TAKE THAT SANDWICH,
AND I'LL BE BACK
IN A LITTLE BIT.

31:55.348 --> 31:56.566
DON'T WORRY ABOUT A THING, OKAY?

31:56.697 --> 31:58.960
[EXCLAIMS] BYE.

32:00.396 --> 32:02.137
-OH. TSK.

32:02.268 --> 32:04.052
HE'S SO CRAZY.

32:04.183 --> 32:05.227
-[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

32:05.358 --> 32:06.228
-HELLO.
-DUDE, WATCH IT.

32:06.359 --> 32:07.316
-EXCUSE ME.

32:17.718 --> 32:20.895
WELL, FINALLY, I'M YOURS.

32:21.026 --> 32:21.896
-GOOD.

32:26.727 --> 32:29.164
-NO MUSTARD. I KNEW IT!

32:34.953 --> 32:38.913
-[CROWD CHEERING]

33:15.428 --> 33:20.563
-♪ WE WERE RUNNIN ROUND
JUST KILLIN' TIME ♪

33:21.434 --> 33:23.001
♪ WELCOME TO THE BATTLEGROUND

33:23.131 --> 33:24.567
-TIMEOUT. TIMEOUT.

33:24.698 --> 33:25.960
-GARNER:
YOU OUT OF GAS ALREADY?

33:26.091 --> 33:27.309
-I JUST THOUGHT OF SOMETHING.

33:27.440 --> 33:29.659
WE GET A SAMPLE
OF THIS GUY'S BLOOD,

33:29.790 --> 33:32.097
AND MATCH IT TO THE BLOOD
UNDER TITO'S FINGERNAILS,

33:32.227 --> 33:33.924
WE CAN NAIL HIM RIGHT HERE.

33:34.055 --> 33:35.883
-YEAH, BUT HOW ARE WE GONNA
GET IT TO THE LAB?

33:38.451 --> 33:40.148
-STEPHANIE CAN GET IT THERE.

33:41.323 --> 33:43.412
-COME ON, GUYS. LET'S GO.

33:43.543 --> 33:46.111
-YEAH, MAN, WE GOT
BETTER THINGS TO DO
THAN WAIT FOR YOU ALL DAY.

33:51.203 --> 33:52.639
-ALL YOU GOTTA DO IS DRAW BLOOD.

33:52.769 --> 33:54.684
-WELL WAIT A SECOND.
THIS WAS YOUR IDEA.

33:54.815 --> 33:56.686
-HE'S YOUR MAN.
YOU'RE GUARDING HIM.

33:56.817 --> 33:58.558
-MY GAME IS FINESSE.
YOU'RE SUPPOSED TO BE
THE ENFORCER.

33:58.688 --> 34:00.429
-I KNEW IT. I KNEW IT.

34:00.560 --> 34:02.823
OKAY, YOU WANT ME
TO TAKE HIM OUT?
I'LL TAKE HIM OUT.

34:03.650 --> 34:05.478
-I'LL DO IT.
-NO, FORGET IT.
I'LL TAKE HIM OUT.

34:05.608 --> 34:08.089
-I SAID I'LL DO IT.
-TOO LATE. I'LL HANDLE IT.

34:08.219 --> 34:09.351
-GOOD LUCK.

34:10.309 --> 34:11.310
-LET'S GO.

34:15.226 --> 34:17.751
♪ HERE COMES TROUBLE

34:30.893 --> 34:32.679
♪ HERE COMES TROUBLE

34:41.382 --> 34:43.168
♪ HERE COMES TROUBLE

34:51.958 --> 34:54.047
♪ HERE COMES TROUBLE

34:55.484 --> 34:56.572
-YES!

35:02.143 --> 35:03.666
♪ HERE COMES TROUBLE

35:12.414 --> 35:14.112
♪ HERE COMES TROUBLE

35:23.033 --> 35:24.600
♪ HERE COMES TROUBLE

35:37.396 --> 35:38.701
RIGHT ON. ALL RIGHT.

35:56.893 --> 35:58.547
-GOD, TREY. YOU OKAY?

36:03.900 --> 36:05.772
-CROWD:
COME ON, TREY!

36:25.270 --> 36:27.446
-YOU HAVE
THE MOST INCREDIBLE EYES
I'VE EVER SEEN.

36:28.011 --> 36:29.883
-REALLY?
-OH, YEAH.
I KNOW ABOUT THESE THINGS.

36:30.013 --> 36:31.101
I'M AN EYE MAN.

36:31.841 --> 36:33.539
I ALMOST BECAME AN OPTICIAN.

36:34.322 --> 36:35.193
-THAT'S INCREDIBLE.

36:36.019 --> 36:37.020
-YEAH.

36:38.935 --> 36:40.110
-OH!

36:41.808 --> 36:42.939
-ARE YOU OKAY?

36:44.376 --> 36:46.595
-LET ME JUST...
I'M A LITTLE WET.
LET ME JUST CLEAN OFF HERE.

36:49.555 --> 36:50.556
-EXCUSE ME.

36:51.209 --> 36:52.601
-ARLENE,
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

36:52.732 --> 36:55.343
-OH, THEY FORGOT TO PUT MUSTARD
ON MY SANDWICH.

36:55.474 --> 36:57.258
-OH, GIVE ME YOUR SANDWICH.
I'LL GET SOME MUSTARD FOR IT.

36:57.389 --> 37:00.261
-OH, HONEY, THIS IS SO GORGEOUS.

37:00.392 --> 37:01.697
-YEAH.
-LOOK.

37:01.828 --> 37:03.743
HEY, WAIT A MINUTE.
I RECOGNIZE HER.

37:03.873 --> 37:06.659
IS THAT...
THAT'S THE LIFEGUARD
FROM THE BEACH.

37:06.789 --> 37:08.138
-LOOK, LET ME GET
SOME MUSTARD, OKAY?

37:08.269 --> 37:09.923
-WAIT A MINUTE.
WHY IS YOUR JACKET THERE?

37:10.489 --> 37:12.404
-I JUST PUT IT DOWN THERE.
NO REASON.

37:13.013 --> 37:14.710
-ARE YOU HAVING LUNCH WITH HER?

37:14.841 --> 37:16.799
-NO. WHAT WOULD MAKE YOU THINK
I'M HAVING LUNCH WITH HER?

37:20.455 --> 37:22.327
-DENNIS, OUR FOOD JUST ARRIVED,
AND IT'S GETTING COLD.

37:23.066 --> 37:25.808
-OH, MY GOD!
HOW COULD YOU DO THIS?

37:25.939 --> 37:27.636
IT'S OUR HONEYMOON!

37:27.767 --> 37:29.203
-YOUR HONEYMOON?

37:29.334 --> 37:30.770
YOU'RE NOT HIS ASSISTANT?

37:30.900 --> 37:32.467
-HIS ASSISTANT?

37:32.598 --> 37:34.513
I'M HIS WIFE!

37:34.643 --> 37:35.949
-HIS WIFE?

37:36.079 --> 37:38.821
-ARLENE, LOOK,
I CAN EXPLAIN EVERYTHING.

37:40.083 --> 37:42.608
I WAS JUST TRYING TO ARRANGE
SOME SWIMMING LESSONS FOR YOU.
TELL HER, C.J.

37:42.738 --> 37:44.131
-[CRYING] TELL ME.

37:48.918 --> 37:50.746
-ARLENE: OH, MY GOD!

37:51.573 --> 37:55.229
-OH, GOD. IT'S EGG SALAD.
I HATE EGG SALAD.

37:55.360 --> 37:56.448
UGH!

37:58.014 --> 38:00.669
UGH! UGH!

38:01.670 --> 38:05.370
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

38:17.773 --> 38:19.079
-HOW DID YOU DO THAT?

38:19.209 --> 38:20.820
-IT'S ALL IN THE WRISTS.

38:28.436 --> 38:30.003
-GAME POINT. LET'S GO.

38:31.309 --> 38:32.962
-D! D!

38:36.052 --> 38:37.489
-GET ON HIM. GET ON HIM.

38:41.754 --> 38:43.321
-YEAH, BABY!

38:45.192 --> 38:47.673
-SORRY, MAN.
-THAT'S ALL RIGHT.
IT'S ALL RIGHT.

38:47.803 --> 38:49.936
-I TOLD YOU BEFORE.
LIFEGUARDS CAN'T JUMP.

38:50.066 --> 38:52.460
-YOU CAN'T JUMP, MAN.
YOU PLAYED THE BOARDS CRAZY.

38:52.591 --> 38:53.853
-GUESS WHAT.
-WHAT?

38:53.983 --> 38:55.245
-YOU GOT YOUR MAN.

38:57.465 --> 38:58.640
THE COPS ARE RIGHT BEHIND ME.

38:58.771 --> 39:00.599
-WE GONNA GET OUR MONEY.

39:04.472 --> 39:06.344
-GARNER: GAME IS REALLY
OVER NOW, TREY.

39:06.909 --> 39:09.912
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

39:21.576 --> 39:23.317
-HEY!
-SLOW DOWN, MAN!

39:33.762 --> 39:36.678
-WHAT'S GOING ON?
-WATCH IT!

40:00.963 --> 40:02.574
-MITCH:
OKAY, IT'S OVER.

40:02.704 --> 40:03.792
IT'S OVER.

40:04.880 --> 40:06.142
GAME IS OVER, PAL.

40:10.495 --> 40:12.453
-NOW, THAT'S HOW
YOU PLAY DEFENSE.

40:13.193 --> 40:15.151
-WHAT WERE
THE ODDS ON US ANYWAY?

40:26.641 --> 40:28.817
-[PANTING]

40:31.429 --> 40:33.126
[STRAINING]

40:33.256 --> 40:36.434
-YOU CAN'T DUNK, MITCH. COME ON.
WHAT ARE YOU TRYING TO DO?

40:37.870 --> 40:39.393
-[STRAINING]

40:41.264 --> 40:43.310
-FORGET IT, MAN. FORGET IT.

40:45.486 --> 40:48.402
-HEY, HEY, HEY, COME ON.
COME ON. WHY ARE YOU
TORTURING YOURSELF, MAN?

40:48.533 --> 40:50.665
IT AIN'T GONNA HAPPEN.
LIFEGUARDS CAN'T JUMP.

40:50.796 --> 40:53.538
-[STRAINING] OR SHOOT.

40:55.453 --> 40:58.020
-I JUST GOT FINISHED TALKING
TO TITO'S WIFE.

40:58.151 --> 41:01.676
TURNED OUT SHE AND TREY
GAVE HIM AN OVERDOSE,
PUSHED HIM OFF THE JETTY.

41:02.938 --> 41:04.723
THOUGHT IT'D MAKE
THEM BOTH RICH.

41:08.030 --> 41:09.554
-A LOT OF THAT
GOING AROUND LATELY.

41:10.119 --> 41:12.644
-YEAH, GETS FRUSTRATING.

41:13.645 --> 41:16.691
-HEY, HEY, HEY, HEY.
I KNOW ONE WAY OF WORKING
THAT FRUSTRATION OFF.

41:16.822 --> 41:18.998
-WHAT'S THAT?

41:19.128 --> 41:21.653
-WHAT DO YOU SAY, YOU AND ME,
ONE-ON-ONE, MAN TO MAN,
RIGHT HERE, RIGHT NOW?

41:21.783 --> 41:25.047
-[LAUGHING]
YOU THINK YOU CAN BEAT ME?

41:25.178 --> 41:26.701
-THERE'S ON WAY TO FIND OUT.

41:26.832 --> 41:28.573
-WHAT'S YOUR SPOT?
HOW MANY POINTS YOU WANT?

41:28.703 --> 41:32.968
-NO SPOTS. NO POINTS. NO ODDS.

41:33.099 --> 41:37.538
JUST YOU AND ME
ONE-ON-ONE RIGHT HERE.
EVEN MONEY.

41:39.453 --> 41:40.454
-LET'S DO IT.

41:40.585 --> 41:42.891
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

41:50.203 --> 41:51.726
-WAIT A MINUTE.
WHAT WAS THAT?

41:52.814 --> 41:54.076
HOW DID HE DO THAT?
